description.narrative: The project objective is to increase production and market access of rural families living in the Chambo and Chanchan-Chimbo river basins within Chimborazo Province, through investments in irrigation and roads improvement.

condition.narrative: Borrower has entered into a trust agreement with the Central Bank of Ecuador and entered into a restitution agreement with theGuarantor
By December 14, 2007, the Borrower has strengthened and updated the financial management system in a manner satisfactory to the Bank
Within 2 weeks after the Effective Date, the Borrower shall ensure that thefinancial management specialist (FM), the FM assistantand the treasury have been appointed
Within 3 months after Effective Date, the Borrower has appointed the senior staff of the procurement unit, submitted to the Bankthe revised budding documents and standard formats for bid evaluation
Within 3 months after the Effective Date, the external financial audit firm will be contracted

comment.narrative: Determine for every subproject request

title.narrative: Average increase in water distribution efficiency on the main distribution line of improved irrigation systems

comment.narrative: Determined for every sub-project

Target overachieved.Efficiency with project is 74%. Efficiency without project was 48.5%. Increase in % is (74-48.5)/48.5 =53%For 55 irrigation schemes.Source: Final impact evaluation assessment (June 2014)

comment.narrative: Determined for every subproject request
Target overachieved.For 55 irrigation schemes.Source: Final impact evaluation assessment (June 2014)

title.narrative: Number of maintenance microenterprises strengthened in techinical and administrative aspects.

comment.narrative: It was decided that the impact would be greater if resources were used to strengthen DAGCHP so that they can directly provide thetining. This allows for longer term results and thus increases sustainability.
cf. Annex 4-Restructuring June 2012.
Target met.Source: Final impact evaluation assessment (June 2014)

title.narrative: Share of rural population with access to an all-season road

comment.narrative: Share of rural population is in relation to the Chimborazo Province total population.
Share of rural population is reported in relation to the Chimborazo Province total population.

title.narrative: Beneficiaries' annual agricultural production value has increased at least by 10% on average in constant prices(Base production value is US$1,560/year/family)

comment.narrative: The initial baseline value (US$ 1,560) has been reviewed after a real analysis was conducted.
Indicator was changed during restructuring in June 2012.
Target overachieved.Source: Final impact evaluation assessment (June 2014)Final number of beneficiaries is 7,900 families

title.narrative: Increase in the cultivation of high-value crops in selected irrigation systems

comment.narrative: There are no improved irrigation systems

Target partially achieved (in progress).The project improved existing irrigation schemes (with more reliable irrigation servicesand increased efficiency) in 4,123 ha and increased the irrigated area (command area) of 562ha. Changes in cultivation is expectedto take some time as the farmers will rely on irrigation services and take risk to invest in high value crops.

title.narrative: Number of families who benefit from improved roads

comment.narrative: This indicator added on June 2012, was designed to show the improved access to roads in the Project area
Target overachieved.Source: Final impact evaluation assessment (June 2014)

title.narrative: 30% average travel time reduction along 50.4 km of roads that are rehabilitated and turned into all-weather roads allowing interconection with main roads.

comment.narrative: Transit on the 50.4km of roads in only seasonal. 60 min. in C-D road, 2h, 40m in Charicando road; 26m in Cujibíes road; 34m inFlores-Y de Achullay road.

Target overachieved.Source: Final impact evaluation assessment (June 2014)Charicando – Cocán – La Dolorosa (from 160 mn to104mn)Quimiag – Cubijies (from 26 to 16mn) and Flores – Y de Achullay (from 34 to 20 mn)

title.narrative: Decrease in O&M costs (%) (base value is cost of light vehicles: US$0.23/km in R-C road and US$0.17/km in C-D roads)

comment.narrative: US$ 0.7/km in Cocán-La Dolorosa road; US$ 0.9/km Cubijíes-Quimiag road; US$ 0.6/km Flores-Y de Achullay road
Target overachieved.1.05 US4/km with project instead of 2.33 US4/km without project.Source: Final impact evaluation assessment(June 2014)
